# WriterOS

Multi-agent writing studio. React + Vite in `src/`. Prototype in `project/` is visual reference only.

## State and I/O

- Read: `useStore(selector)` from `src/lib/store.js`.
- Write: `window.WOS.store.actions.*` only.
- Network: `src/lib/bridge.js` only. **Never import `bridge.js` from UI components.**

## Agents

- Triage is the only router. Specialists file handoffs; they do not invoke each other.
- Respect `agent.writes` scope as a permission boundary.
- Shared truth lives in `ProjectState` — no side channels.

## Memory

- `canon`: immutable except Zoe.
- `pinned`: requires user approval to delete.
- Do not conflate memory classes.

## Implementation style

- Match prototype visuals, not prototype file structure.
- Ambiguous scope: ask before large changes.
- Prefer small, reviewable diffs. Reuse existing functions before adding parallel copies.
- For third-party APIs: use `opensrc` / `repos/` source — do not guess.

## Phase work

Load `docs/HANDOFF.md` when starting a new roadmap phase, not every session.
